vanessa-adt (0.0.8-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Debian Changes from Upstream
    - Update from standards version 3.7.2 to 3.8.2
    - Use ${binary:Version} instead of ${Source-Version}
    - Remove dependency on libc6-dev
    - Remove trailing whitespace from description of libvanessa-adt0
    - Run make distclean conditonally, rather than ignoring _all_ errors it
      may produce
    - Update copyright file
      - Use LGPL 2.1, as per COPYING file
    - Exit postinst on error by setting -e in script
    - Don't use ./mkinstalldirs as it may not exist
    - Move libvanessa-adt-dev to section libdevel
    - Use Debconf 7
  * non-Debian Changes from Upstream
    - Use AC_PROG_LIBTOOL instead of AM_PROC_LIBTOOL in configure.am
    - Rename configure.in as configure.ac
    - Don't use AC_PROG_RANLIB in configure.ac, it isn't needed
    - Remove files from EXTRA_DIST that are included in the distribution
      anyway
    - Update COPYTING file to the recent text for the LGPL v2.1
    - Update inline copyright information
      - Update years to cover up to 2008
      - Always include email address with name
      - Use name rather than nickname
    - Resolve various libtoolize warnings

 -- Simon Horman <horms@debian.org>  Thu, 13 Aug 2009 19:55:51 +1000

